item.title: Interview with Prathamesh Chavan
item.author: Parth Goswami
item.description: We have many diverse contributors here at Red Hat that help upstream communities in unconventional ways that don’t require any coding or development skills. Starting with a non-code contribution can help anyone overcome the sense of failure and not being good enough, and it can also serve as a springboard for our open source adventure. This article aims to highlight some non-code open source contributions that anyone can make right now to get started contributing.
